[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'gvwilson', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2017-01-25T00:17:54Z', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': '', 'title': 'Blog post about government scientists under attack', 'type': 'issue'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'jduckles', 'comment_id': 275118512.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-25 14:16:41+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'I dislike this as much or more than you, but our blog is not the the place for this, please reserve this kind of position for your personal blog.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'gvwilson', 'comment_id': 275132082.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-25 15:07:11+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'I believe an overwhelming majority of our instructors would support us taking some sort of public stand on suppression of science.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'k8hertweck', 'comment_id': 275145070.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-25 15:51:07+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': "Given this is an issue related to the overall vision of SWC, and therefore a strategic decision, I'd be interested to hear what the other members of the Steering Committee have to say: @username_6 @JasonJWilliamsNY @weaverbel @username_5 @username_4 @username_3", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'jduckles', 'comment_id': 275147239.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-25 15:57:48+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'Under 501(c)3 rules we have to be VERY careful about anything like endorsements/criticisms of candidates in political elections in the USA. Without an expert on staff about these kinds of things this is best left up to personal opinion and not official opinions of the organization. Crappy but true. We really don't want to go there at the size we are as an organization. Most of this has to do with candidacy, but the political reality is our fiscal sponsor is a 501(c)3 and we can't do this. Orgs like the ACLU are 501(c)4, they can do this as long as it isn't their primary focus. Believe me, we don't want to "go there" in an official  capacity in our current legal structuring.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'jduckles', 'comment_id': 275148367.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-25 16:01:27+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "Additionally your post explicitly names an individual who was and presumably will again be a candidate in a US election and takes a position against him. Believe me, I hate the fact that political speech is not free speech for certain types of organizations in America. However I don't want the organization to come tumbling down because the IRS says we overreached here.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'jduckles', 'comment_id': 275153486.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-25 16:18:43+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "For what we can and can't do [this article is](https://www.nolo.com/legal-encyclopedia/limits-political-campaigning-501c3-nonprofits-29982.html) great.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'karinlag', 'comment_id': 275157536.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-25 16:32:21+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_3', 'text': "Thankyou Jonah for clarifying this, this is most useful.

For me personally, regardless of the legal ramifications for the SCF, I would be very hesitant to go into these things. Although our mission could be considered political, we are not a political organization.  I could see us speaking up about knowledge actually being deleted and thus lost, but that's just about it.

However, I would love to see something about this on the discuss list and on our personal blogs/twitter accounts. We as individuals can and should speak up.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'raynamharris', 'comment_id': 275315350.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-26 06:14:58+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_4', 'text': 'I would have to say I side with @username_1 and @username_3 on this one and say it is best posted on a personal blog. Even if (most) everyone is the community would support this, I am weary of posting something political with "we" in the title that was written by a single individual member of the community. However, like @username_2 said, if this is part of the strategic mission, then it could be approached strategically.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'rgaiacs', 'comment_id': 275665086.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-27 13:28:58+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_5', 'text': "I'm on @username_1, @username_3 and @username_4 side.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'BillMills', 'comment_id': 275785442.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-27 21:54:28+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': "Team,

Jonah has a point - we do have a responsibility to the SCF as an entity
worth defending. But under no circumstances should we submit to
intimidation.

I propose that we adopt this post on each of our personal blogs, and issue
a joint statement, not as affiliates of Software Carpentry, but as
individuals refusing to be belittled, cowed, or shut down by a bully. Risk
is our new reality; while it isn't right to ask the SCF to wear that risk,
each of us can choose for themselves, and let subtext do the talking.
Anyone who wants to make a coordinated statement, contact me.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'raynamharris', 'comment_id': 275821548.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-28 02:37:57+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_4', 'text': 'Thanks @username_6 I like this suggestion a lot! Power in numbers.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'k8hertweck', 'comment_id': 275885119.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-29 00:31:53+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': "After discussing the issue with folks working at other nonprofits and reading the IRS rules, it seems to me like it would be within our rights to describe an SCF stance on issues without indicting specific individuals. However, it's clear that most of our leadership isn't comfortable with the potential for risk or reprisal such a statement might bring. Thanks to Jonah for clarifying the rationale for rejection of the original post, and I am happy to contribute to coordinated, personal posts as @username_6 suggests.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'k8hertweck', 'comment_id': 275939776.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-29 19:34:42+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': '@username_0, do we have your permission to adapt your language from this post, and if so, how would you like for us to attribute credit to you?', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'gvwilson', 'comment_id': 275942948.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-29 20:21:44+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'Of course - I've published it separately at 
http://third-bit.com/2017/01/25/stand-with-govt-scientists.html. 
According to 
https://twitter.com/CHURCHLADY320/status/825581552864161792, 501(c)3's 
can criticize government policy as long as they refer to "The Executive 
Branch" or "The White House" rather than "the Trump Administration" or 
"the President", or alternatively simply say, "This policy will be 
harmful to..."', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'BillMills', 'comment_id': 275943163.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-29 20:24:45+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': "OK - what I'm really hearing here, is that it's time to summon legal aide. Who has lawyer friends? I do, but they're pretty slammed right now with similar projects. If nothing else, getting a pro bono in to help us understand precisely what the SCF should be scared of and what we can be bold on should help our institutional confidence on an issue that will come up again; what happens when partners or colleague organizations, for example, ask us to take a stance with them and we waffle? Even if this particular post isn't for us, the muddy waters already articulated in this thread need clearing up so we have a better idea of how to maneuver in future. While we do have a responsibility to protect the SCF, our position as the representatives of a huge and vibrant community also sets to us a broader civic responsibility to speak when speaking's needed. A strictly sit-down-and-shut-up defensive policy falls down on that responsibility.

I'll reach out to folks on other channels to discuss non-SCF backed statements; anyone who wants to join, you know where to find me.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'karinlag', 'comment_id': 275950823.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-29 22:16:58+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_3', 'text': 'All things considered, I have changed my mind. I think that the SCF should
create a statement on this. Considering our mission statement I think we
could and should focus on the way this administration deals with scientific
facts,  and that they are restricting travel, which will always be
detrimental to scientific progress.

Best,  Karin', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'raynamharris', 'comment_id': 275975958.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-30 04:02:06+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_4', 'text': "I reposted Greg's blog without modification except for note at the bottom about it being a reproduction. https://medium.com/@username_4/stand-with-government-scientists-970373e9c211#.z713gcc2x

The UT Austin president just published a statement today that doesn't say a whole lot in terms of action but does that he values everyone in the community and offers avenues of support for those that need it
https://medium.com/@username_4/stand-with-government-scientists-970373e9c211#.z713gcc2x", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'BillMills', 'comment_id': 276166533.0, 'datetime': '2017-01-30 19:36:50+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': "Excellent examples, @username_4 - I think this warrants a discussion in person. I don't see anything on our calendar for February, but perhaps an auxiliary meeting is in order if we don't have an official meeting left. I recommend an official stance framed as an open letter per Rayna's examples.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
